sentences: Barbara Alexandra "Sandra" Reemer (17 October 1950 – 6 June 2017) was an Indo-Dutch singer and television presenter.
Barbara Alexandra "Sandra" Reemer (17 October 1950 – 6 June 2017) was an Indo-Dutch singer and television presenter.
In 1972, she sang the song "Als het om de liefde gaat" in a duet with Dries Holten (she was credited as "Sandra", he was credited as "Andres"); the duo came fourth.
In 1976, this time credited under her real name, Reemer performed solo singing the song "The Party's Over", which reached ninth place.
In 1979, she was credited as "Xandra" and sang the song "Colorado", which placed twelfth.
She later returned to the contest to sing backing vocals (uncredited) for the Dutch entry in 1983, "Sing Me A Song", performed by Bernadette.
She died on 6 June 2017, following a long battle with breast cancer.
